@*
    MAINLAYOUT — Blazor Concept: LayoutComponentBase + @Body (RenderFragment)

    React equivalent: MainLayout.tsx with {children}
    Angular equivalent: main-layout.component.ts with <ng-content>

    Key Blazor concepts:
    1. @inherits LayoutComponentBase — Makes this a layout component
       This base class provides the @Body property (a RenderFragment).
       Blazor renders the matched page component in place of @Body.

       React equivalent:  function Layout({ children }) { return <div>{children}</div> }
       Angular equivalent: <ng-content /> (content projection)

    2. @Body — RenderFragment (Blazor's {children})
       RenderFragment is Blazor's type for "renderable content" — like React.ReactNode.
       The Router (in App.razor) renders page components into @Body.

       Blazor:  @Body
       React:   {children}
       Angular: <ng-content />

    3. Layout is set in App.razor via DefaultLayout="@typeof(MainLayout)"
       React:   <Route element={<MainLayout />}> wraps child routes
       Angular: AppComponent template includes <router-outlet>
*@
@inherits LayoutComponentBase

<div class="layout">
    <NavMenu />
    <main class="main-content">
        @* @Body renders the current page component — like React's {children} *@
        @Body
    </main>
</div>
